import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['Body_Mass__g_'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Body_Mass__g_'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Body_Mass__g_'])
    ax = data.boxplot(column='Body_Mass__g_', by='Species', rot=45)
    ax.set_xlabel('Species')
    ax.set_ylabel('Body Mass (g)')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass across different penguin species?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Body_Mass__g_'] = pd.to_numeric(data['Body_Mass__g_'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['Body_Mass__g_'])
    male_data = data[data['Sex'] == 'MALE']['Body_Mass__g_']
    female_data = data[data['Sex'] == 'FEMALE']['Body_Mass__g_']
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist([male_data, female_data], bins=20, label=['Male', 'Female'])
    plt.xlabel('Body Mass (g)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of body mass for male and female penguins?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
